cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of learning functions over sets, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a novel architecture called SPAN that simultaneously learns the function as well as adversarial or worst-case permutations for each input set. This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
